(1) An NCII entity shall—
(a) implement and maintain cyber security measures to protect the national critical information infrastructure;
(b) comply with any standards, codes of practice and directives issued under this Act;
(c) report any cyber security incident to the Chief Executive in accordance with this Act;
(d) conduct or cause to be conducted cyber security risk assessments in accordance with this Act;
(e) conduct or cause to be conducted cyber security audits in accordance with this Act;
(f) provide information as required by the Chief Executive or the NCII sector lead; and
(g) comply with any other duty as may be prescribed.
(2) Failure to comply with subsection (1) shall constitute an offence and the NCII entity shall, on conviction, be liable to a fine not exceeding five hundred thousand ringgit or to imprisonment for a term not exceeding ten years or to both.

(1) An NCII sector lead shall—
(a) coordinate and monitor the cyber security of national critical information infrastructure in its sector;
(b) develop and recommend codes of practice for its sector;
(c) advise NCII entities in its sector on cyber security matters;
(d) report to the Chief Executive on the state of cyber security in its sector;
(e) assist NCII entities in its sector in complying with this Act; and
(f) comply with any other duty as may be prescribed.
(2) An NCII sector lead may issue guidelines to NCII entities in its sector on matters relating to cyber security.
